descript.abstract: The Virginia Institute of Marine Science published the first Tidal marsh Inventories for the City of Virginia Beach in 1989 using data collected in the 1970's. Using high resolution color infra-red imagery from 2009 and 2011 a new Tidal Marsh Inventory has been developed for 2012. Marsh boundaries were generated using heads-up digitizing techniques at a scale of 1:1,000. Each marsh polygon was classified by morphologic type: fringe, extensive, embayed, or marsh island. Marshes were ground-truthed in the field where a community type index was assigned to each marsh based on plant community make-up.
descript.purpose: To maintain and update an inventory of the distribution of tidal marshes for the Commonwealth f Virginia.
descript.supplinf: Imagery used to generate the tidal marsh boundaries is a product of the Virginia Base Mapping Program of the Virginia Information Technology Agency.

procstep.procdesc: The 2012 TMI (Tidal Marsh Inventory) shapefile was created by visual photo interpretation and heads up digitizing of recent (2009 and 2011) high resolution (6") infrared aerial photography at a scale of 1:1000. This scale was picked as a compromise between taking full advantage of the resolution and time constraints. Marsh information from previous shoreline surveys was used, particularly in identifying narrow fringe marshes. The latest NWI was also used. This delineation was completed prior to the fieldwork and then corrected as noted in the field.
